inn1.comm: on the middle and leg, worked nicely to deep backward square leg, comes back slowly for the second run.
pushes forward to mid-off.
That one bounced a bit extra and cramped Jayasuriya for room. Thick indise edge
Moved away from Jayasuriya a fraction. Play and miss outside off stump
Full on the pads. Clipped straight to mid-on
First boundary of the innings, smacked to the midwicket fence.
Slightly short of a length and Jayasuriya attempts to hit over mid-off. Doesn't get hold of it and just manages to clear the fielder for a couple of runs.
Played to cover.
Cut to third man. Slightly uppish but in the gap.
Tight line on off stump. No room for Sangakkara who plays it back to the bowler.

Room offered on this ocassion and Sangakkara leans on to the front foot and 
eases it past cover for four.
Defended on the leg side
Gone. Huge wicket that. Slightly shorter in length and Jayasuriya whips it off his pads in the air and straight down third man's throat.
Played towards point off the back foot
Defended to point again
Played back down the pitch
Wide outside off stump and Jayawardene slashes. thick outside edge flies down to third man.
Defended to midwicket
Width offered outside off stump. Jayawardene waits on it and cuts it late square of the third man fielder who has no chance.
Defended back to the bowler
Wide again and Jayawardene goes at it hard but hits it straight to cover
Played towards point
Jayawardene plays and misses outside off stump
Played with an angled bat to point
Played to mid- on
Clipped off his pads and beautifully timed past midwicket for four. That was a gentle push that raced away.
Played to midwicket and Jayawardene wants the single. Sangakkara send him back and it would have been tight had there been a direct hit.
Played off the front foot to mid-off
Played to point
Defended to mid-off, good come back from Mashrafe
Slightly short of a length and Jayawardene goes on the front foot and punches it to cover.
Drifting on to the pads. Jayawardene leans across and plays it to midwicket.
Better line on off stump. Jayawardene plays it towards cover but cant find the gap.
Jayawardene steps down and creates room outside off stump and slashes it away to the cover fence.
Clipped past square leg for a couple of runs.
Steered to third man.
Tried to run it to third man but did not make proper contact. Single taken to where short third man would have been.
Played back to the bowler.
Defended on the front foot on the offside.
Full on off stump. Played to cover. Defended on the front foot.
Played towards point.
Defended on the offside.
Rapped on the pads but drifting down leg
Played to cover
Driven to cover who gets a hand on it and pushes it wide off  mid off for a couple of runs
Played behind square leg
Square driven to point where Kapali dives to his right and saves runs.
Hit in the air to third man
Rasel oversteps to concede the first extra of the innings.
Played on the off side for no run.
Steered towards point
Played off the back foot towards point for no run
Hit to cover.
Dropped! Jayawardene tried to run it to third man and gets the outside edge but it bounces off Mashuds glove.
Tries a similar shot and connects well this time. Played to third man.
Chipped over the infield and it runs away to the midwicket fence.
Driven on the up but straight to the cover fielder
Driven on the rise off the front foot to mid-off
Attempted yorker. Well dug out back to the bowler.
Clipped of the pads straight to square leg
Turned past square leg of his hips for a single.
Slightly shorter and wide outside off stump. Sangakkara latches on to the width and slashes it through cover and the ball speeds to the fence.
Hit straight to the cover fielder.
Glanced off his pads to fine leg for another single.
Full on middle stump. Jayawardene opens the face and angles it to point.
Played to point again
Way down leg side .Wide called.
Opened the face and runs it down to third man.
Drifting down leg side again. Another wide.
Full and straight and Jayawardene drives down the ground. It was in the air but safe past the bowler and runs down to the long-on fence.
Wide outside off stump and Jayawardene goes hard at it and carves it through point for four.
Full and angling in to the pads. Played to mid-on
Very wide outside off stump and Jayawardene goes on the front foot and thumps it through cover for four.
Thick outside edge to third man while attempting the cover drive.
Played back to the bowler.
That one stopped on Jayawardene a bit. Loops in the air short of cover.
Played on the off side off the front foot.
Drifting down leg this time and steered to short fine leg.
This time he plays it wide of the short fine leg fielder for a single
Defended to midwicket
Short and wide again from Baisya. Jayawardene helps himself to a boundary by crashing it between cover and point.
Overcompensating for the room offered the previous ball by drifting on to the pads, Jayawardene chips it over square leg for another boundary.
Played on the off side for a single.
Defended to midwicket.
Dabbed on the offside and a sharp single is taken to the cover fielder.
Played towards point.
Tucked to short fine leg for a quick single. Theres a direct hit at the non-strikers end but Sangakkara is quite safe.
Dabbed on the offside, looking for the single but decide against it.
Played to wide mid-on for a single.
Flicked past square leg for an attempted two. There is a mix up on the second run but a wide throw at the keepers end saves the Sangakkara.
Played to cover.
Dabbed on the on side for a single.
Driven back to the bowler.
Driven to long on for a single.
Full toss played past midwicket for a single.
Defended on the off side
Played to long on for a single.
Hit off the back foot to long on for another single.
Single taken to long-off and that brings up jayawardenes fifty. Well Played.
Turned past square leg for one run.
Dabbed behind square for a single.
Stepped down the track and played wide of midwicket.
Single taken to short third man.

That one stopped on Jayawardene a touch and he only manages to loop in back tamely to the bowler who takes a good catch given that Sangakkara was in the way. Just as Jayawardene was milking the singles, Bangladesh have managed to dislodge him.
Played to short fine leg.
Hit hard, but straight to cover.
Played down the ground for a single.
Played back to the bowlers
Single taken to long-on, Sangakkara picking the ones off with ease.
Defended on the offside.
Goes down on one knee and lofts it over midwicket for a huge six.
And again. This time along the ground through midwicket for four.
Played to midwicket for an easy single.
Turned fine off his legs for two to fine leg.
Tried to play a sweep but changed his mind at the last minute. Beaten outside off stump.
Defended to cover.
Swept to short fine leg.
Wide outside off stump. Batsman tries to cut but misses.
Played towards cover.
Turned on the leg side for another single.
Full on the pads. Sangakkara clips past midwicket for a single.
Outside off stump and Lokuarachchi tries to sweep and misses.
Dabbed off the back foot to midwicket for a single.
Defended to midwicket.
Driven on the front foot to long-on. Another single taken.
Single taken to square leg.
Lokuarachchi tries to step down but decides against it. Chops it to cover.
Single taken to deep midwicket.
Dabbed towards point for a single.
Single taken to cover.
Tossed up, Sangakkara waited for it and plays it to long-on for a single.
Pulled to midwicket for a single.
Swept for deep-backward square leg for a single.
Outside off stump. Played off the back foot straight to cover.
Single taken to the deep cover fielder.
Dabbed to midwicket for a single.
Played back down the pitch.
Driven to long-off for a single. Sangakkara reaches a patient half-century.
Swept to deep backward square for a single.
Played off the back foot to midwicket for a single.
Turned to square leg for another single. Sri lanka accumulating the runs easily.
Cut off the back foot to sweeper. Batsmen almost collide while going to the second run but the danger is averted.
Wide outside off stump and Loukarachchi pulls it in the air to midwicket. The batsmen run one to bring up Lokuarachchi;s half-century.
Played off the back foot to midwicket.
Cut to deep point for a single
Turned off his legs to short fine leg for a sharp single.
Driven off the back foot straight to the bowler.
Bowled! Stright ball on middle stump. Lokuarachchi tries to slog sweep it and misses completely and is bowled. Hes gone after doing a superb job of upping the tempo of the innings.
Cut past point for a single.
Wide outside leg stump. Called wide.
Turned off his pads for a single.
Played through cover off the backfoot for a single. That brings up the 200.
Straight and full. Played back past the bowler for a single. That wasnt timed well at all.
Wide outside off stump, Sangakkara tried to turn it on the leg side and got an outside edge down to third man.
Driven down the ground to long off
Tried the pull shot but got a thick inner edge past the stumps to third man for four.
And again. This time he tried to drive and gets the inside edge for four to third man. Lucky breaks for Sangakkara.
Clipped past square leg. Misfield allows a couple of extra runs.
Swept to deep midwicket
Turned behind square for one.
Another inside edge. This time off Dilshans attempted drive. The ball runs down to fine leg for four.
Played to midwicket.
Shorter length and Dilshan latches on to it with the pull and sends the ball screeching to the deep backward square fence.
Driven to long-off for a single.
Slower ball but wide outside off stump and it is called by the umpire.
Chipped in the air but it falls safe at mid-on. The batsmen scamper two and theres a direct hit at the strikers end but Sangakkara is safe.
Wide ball down legside. Keeper only manages to get a glove on it and the batsmen run one.
Tried to hit the ball hard but didnt time it well. Single to cover.
Full and Sangakkara swings it off his pads to the deep square leg fence for one.
Short ball and easy meat for Dilshan who pulls it for four.
Gone. Dilshan attempts a cheeky paddle sweep and paddles it straight up in the air to short fine leg.
Full and swinging in to Sangakkara who misses the flick and is struck on the pad. Batsmen take a single after the ball bounces off the pad to short third man.
Sangakkara tries to heave it on the leg side and misses.
He tries the heave again, connects this time and sends it hard over midwicket. Poor fielding on the boundary concedes a boundary.
Bowled! Tried the slog sweep and didnt connect. The ball brushes his shirt and crashes into the stumps. Sangakkara goes for 109.
Beaten by the turn. Single taken to short fine leg.
Cut to the deep point fielder for one.
Single taken to short fine leg.
Driven down the ground
Full toss outside off stump. Batsman has a go at it and misses.
Full ball and smashed! Straight hit down the ground and it clears long off with ease
Drifting on to his pads and Kapudegera times it well to the deep square leg fence.
Pushed to long on and good running between the wickets!
Played to square leg
Kapugedera tries to go airborne again. Gets a thick outside edge down to third man.
Fullish ball and the batsman tries to heave it through midwicket and doesnt connect.
Caught! Kapugedera, searching for the boundary, carves it in the air straight to the cover fielder.
Outside edge goes to third man for a single.
Played to long-on for one
Six! Massive slog over midwicket. Maharoof connects perfectly and the ball sails clear of the ropes.
Single taken to point.
Another massive blow. Waited for the shorter ball, rocked on to the back foot and bashed it over long-on for six.
Short ball and Maharoof drills the pull through midwicket all the way to the fence. Huge over this for Sri Lanka. The score goes past 300.
Single to long-on
Colossal hit! Outside off stump and Maharoof biffs it off the back foot and his sheer power sends the ball flying over long-on. Sri Lanka end the innings in some style!
